&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Please note that we will never request payment or bank account information at any stage of the recruitment process. As we continue to grow our teams, we urge you to be cautious of fraudulent job postings or recruitment activities that misuse our company name and information. Please protect your personal information during any recruitment process. While Monks may contact potential candidates via LinkedIn, all applications must be submitted through our official website (&lt;a class=&quot;c-link c-link--focus-visible&quot; href=&quot;http://monks.com/careers&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;http://monks.com/careers&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;monks.com/careers&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Monks is a new breed of media consultancy that partners with global brands and agencies seeking transformative marketing results in a time of significant disruption and opportunity. Recognized as a global leader in advanced marketing and advertising technologies, MightyHive provides consulting and services in the areas of media operations and training, data strategy, and analytics.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking an Accountant to join the Corporate team. This busy, hands-on role will be a key part of the regional Finance team and offers a range of responsibilities including managing the day-to-day financial operations, month end accounting and compliance. This is a full-time position and you’ll enjoy being part of a collaborative, supportive and results driven team that thrives in a dynamic and fast paced environment.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities include(but not limited to):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Accounting and Reporting&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain the General Ledger Accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Fixed Asset/Prepayment/Expense Accrual schedules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Balance Sheet reconciliations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reconcile COGS accrual and bills on a monthly basis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage month end closing and statutory financial reporting accurately to meet reporting deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and analysis of the Balance Sheet and Profit and Loss accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preparation and lodgement of payroll tax and BAS/IAS/GST/VAT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with consolidating quarter/half year/year end accounts and prepare papers for the S4 group&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with financial analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tax and Audit&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with the external tax advisory for any withholding tax (GST/CIT) implications in the existing and new markets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with statutory tax lodgement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the Global and local statutory audit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Governance&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and improve process and internal controls, following up the mitigating action of internal control weaknesses&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the external bookkeepers/vendors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with ad hoc tasks and any other activities directed by Management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you bring to it&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelors in Finance/Accounting or related fields&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years accounting experience, 1+ years post qualification experience with a similar role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;APAC experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPA preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work under pressure to meet dead

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Please note that we will never request payment or bank account information at any stage of the recruitment process. As we continue to grow our teams, we urge you to be cautious of fraudulent job postings or recruitment activities that misuse our company name and information. Please protect your personal information during any recruitment process. While Monks may contact potential candidates via LinkedIn, all applications must be submitted through our official website (&lt;a class=&quot;c-link c-link--focus-visible&quot; href=&quot;http://monks.com/careers&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;http://monks.com/careers&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;monks.com/careers&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accountant&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Hybrid, Bogotá, Colombia.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;.Monks Technology Services, part of Media.Monks and S4 Capital, is a global consulting firm mastering AI-powered transformations for the Fortune 100. We combine long-term strategic thinking, deep enterprise experience, and a human-centered approach to help clients transform business processes and dominate their industries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our commitment to inclusion and in compliance with Law 2466 of 2025 from Colombia, we have available spaces for people with disabilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Accountant will be responsible for managing and maintaining accurate financial records, ensuring compliance with accounting standards and company policies. This role will support the Finance department in preparing financial statements, managing reconciliations, and assisting with audits and reporting requirements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Record, classify, and reconcile financial transactions&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;in the accounting system, including AP, AR, payroll, journal entries, and general ledger activity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prepare and review monthly reconciliations&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;for bank accounts, suppliers, customers, and general ledger accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ensure compliance&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;with local tax regulations and support the preparation of tax filings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prepare monthly, quarterly, and annual financial reports&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;in accordance with company policies and accounting standards, including GAAP and/or IFRS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support month-end and year-end closing processes&lt;/strong&gt;, including accruals, adjustments, and required reporting activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Assist with budgeting and forecasting&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;by providing accurate and timely financial data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate with external auditors&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;by preparing schedules, documentation, and supporting materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monitor internal controls&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;and ensure adherence to financial policies and procedures&lt;/li&gt;
